<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7665] JsonSlurperCharSource decimal parsing producing unexpected results</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7665</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the JsonParserType.CHARACTER_SOURCE decimal numbers are first parsed to double value and that value is used to construct the BigDecimal to return.  This can produce some unexpected results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&#8203;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.json.*

def parser = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; JsonSlurper().setType(JsonParserType.CHARACTER_SOURCE)
def json = parser.parseText(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;{&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;num&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: 123.40}&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; json.num &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; BigDecimal
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; 123.40G == json.num&#8203;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fails with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Assertion failed: 

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; 123.40G == json.num
               |  |    |
               |  |    123.400000000000005684341886080801486968994140625
               |  [num:123.400000000000005684341886080801486968994140625]
               &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;

	at Script1.run(Script1.groovy:8)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
